## ARCHITECTURE NOTES
- Abstract the OpenClaw API calls into a /lib/openclaw-client.ts service layer 
  so the transport (REST vs WebSocket) can be swapped without touching UI code
- Use environment variables for OPENCLAW_HOST, OPENCLAW_PORT, OPENCLAW_API_KEY
- If OpenClaw does not natively expose an API, scaffold a lightweight proxy 
  service (Node or Python FastAPI) that sits in the same Docker network and 
  exposes the required endpoints
- Structure the project cleanly:
  /app           → Next.js pages and layouts
  /components    → Reusable UI components
  /lib           → API clients, helpers, types
  /hooks         → Custom React hooks
  /store         → Zustand stores
  /types         → Shared TypeScript interfaces

